ASYNC LOOP LEDGER
=================

Master Mission (Do Not Stop Until Done)
- Move ERP to staging/predeployment readiness with enterprise-grade safety and accounting trust.
- Continue autonomous loop until completion gates are met; do not stop at partial fixes.
- Scope includes: debugging, cybersecurity flaws, business-logic flaws/abuse, accounting integrity, cross-module workflows, duplicate/redundant logic, DB/performance hardening, and release readiness.

Non-Stop Operating Rules
- After each completed step: update plan + append this file.
- Every code change must be committed.
- After each commit: run `codex review --commit <sha>` and log result here.
- Prioritize exploitable vulnerabilities and accounting/invariant failures over cosmetic work.
- Validate by targeted abuse + invariant tests, not doc assumptions.
- Auto-replenish rule: whenever one planned task is marked completed, immediately add at least one new concrete task slice.
- Backlog floor: always keep at least 3 `ready` tasks so loop never runs out of work.
- DB migration policy (mandatory): use Flyway V2 only (`classpath:db/migration_v2`, table `flyway_schema_history_v2`) for all new schema/index fixes.
- No legacy migration additions while in this loop.

Completion Gates (Required For "Safe To Deploy" Claim)
- No known critical/high security issues in auth/RBAC/tenant isolation/data exposure.
- Accounting safety gates hold:
  - Double-entry balance invariants
  - Subledger-GL reconciliation invariants
  - Settlement and reversal idempotency + period-close boundaries
  - Cross-module posting links (sales/inventory/purchasing/payroll -> accounting)
- No confirmed cross-tenant / cross-partner IDOR or privilege abuse paths.
- DB/predeploy gates:
  - migration safety checked (Flyway V2 path)
  - critical indexes and heavy query paths reviewed
  - no committed secrets in runtime config
  - migration overlap/drift scans pass for V2 (`scripts/flyway_overlap_scan.sh --migration-set v2`, `scripts/schema_drift_scan.sh --migration-set v2`)
- Module workflow gates:
  - intended E2E workflows execute with expected state transitions
  - edge-case failures are deterministic and fail-safe

